The paper deals with problems related to constructing planar geometric graphs on a set of points, which is a topic in computational geometry (cs.CG). The use of algorithms and complexity analysis suggests that it could also belong to the sub-categories of data structures (cs.DS) and numerical analysis (cs.NA). The paper also involves proving results related to connectivity and graph theory, which could place it in the sub-categories of discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and game theory (cs.GT).
